Certain topics have not yet reached book form in any depth. Some examples are
(i) Montgomery&#x27;s pair correlation conjecture and the work that initiated from it,
(ii) the new results of Goldston, Pintz and Yilidrim on small gaps between primes, and
(iii) the Green–Tao theorem showing that arbitrarily long arithmetic progressions of primes exist.</text><links>
